parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Anti-Lock Braking System (ABS) Failure on Wet Pavement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system on wet pavement can cause the wheels to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The ABS system fails to engage on wet pavement
the vehicle experiences reduced braking performance
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Insufficient clearance to depress the brake pedal can cause the driver to be unable to stop the vehicle in a timely manner, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal is difficult to press
the brake pedal requires excessive force to press
the driver's foot hits the floor or other obstructions while trying to press the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front frame can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to operate
the vehicle's structural integrity is compromised
unusual noises or vibrations are present while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the automatic transmission to engage can cause the vehicle to stall or not move, which can lead to accidents, especially when merging onto a busy road or when driving uphill.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or refuses to move after a cold start
the transmission slips or hesitates before engaging
the vehicle stalls or shuts off after starting
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations.
